<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_bb59ab05-988a-4e27-9261-9c80fa1b0099" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>G5P1</sptc><title id="_af44548d-9b2f-4ebf-86b8-c3a9906ba05c">Bushfire resistance</title><archive-num>2019: GP5.1</archive-num><subclause id="_2353ce25-16b3-4746-b794-6014860b7da0" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_99e94a37-7ba4-44ea-98b2-f3f4d96ec71b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A building that is constructed in a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1243_0.6.0.xml#_2c223137-7ce5-4993-bd69-503e243c9453" id="_6ac55b2f-af2d-4669-b88a-9c1df1f15a83" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">designated bushfire prone area</xref> must be designed and constructed to—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_ae02ea1d-6505-4349-980f-3956882a59b8">reduce the risk of ignition from a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/5142_0.4.0.xml#_a94e2dcb-1ce6-4b6f-8494-5a82782fc617" id="_9f4b5571-0388-48a4-9a63-544a616e9ecf" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">design bushfire</xref> with an annual exceedance probability not more than 1:100 years, or 1:200 years for a Class 9 building; and</li><li id="_abef83eb-e9ab-4cdb-9bb5-42638c99d156">take account of the assessed duration and intensity of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/5141_0.7.0.xml#_a787835e-2f09-4a54-a85c-40e79b54fd1d" id="_5ef700db-a109-47ce-9915-01e2b98952a9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">fire actions</xref> of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/5142_0.4.0.xml#_a94e2dcb-1ce6-4b6f-8494-5a82782fc617" id="_b5aadd2f-7339-410c-b121-793df8502fb7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">design bushfire</xref>; and</li><li id="_dc8f9340-4e0b-436a-902b-63fdbc7e3fa2">be designed to prevent internal ignition of the building and its contents; and</li><li id="_a938f5e8-e026-4c2c-8e79-b8f7cc757020">maintain the structural integrity of the building for the duration of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/5142_0.4.0.xml#_a94e2dcb-1ce6-4b6f-8494-5a82782fc617" id="_abf1e8d9-3f54-43bb-8a1b-e3602c58896f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">design bushfire</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_d7f92e81-6aa2-40ff-bc5f-07391ef7d57d"><callout-type ncc-info-type="application"/><p>G5P1 applies in a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1243_0.6.0.xml#_7fdc72da-0dba-4321-a799-30448b114125" id="_2509fac4-f242-42fe-adef-c96145b3c468" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">designated bushfire prone area</xref> to—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_7aefcdde-3e80-4777-8179-5977e8f14c11">a Class 2 or 3 building; and</li><li id="_9b74aee7-728f-4a76-bde2-080f764010d6">a Class 9a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1333_0.4.0.xml#_7c7ce523-6325-4d18-90aa-74b36524e738" id="_a6f1da31-ade1-4333-8de9-de197c928365" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">health-care building</xref>; and</li><li id="_02ca8b77-3114-48e3-91ab-8a6705fe5147">a Class 9b—<ol><li id=""><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1251_2.3.0.xml#_0eb2a51d-1d07-416a-890e-1c36a26bbf37" id="_224a3b8c-b757-42d9-8a21-a2e31e16e19c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">early childhood centre</xref>; and</li><li>primary or secondary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1447_0.6.0.xml#_74daea46-04b3-49e7-95bc-eab0207313f1" id="_b366fe2d-456d-4476-80f9-928cba23893c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">school</xref>; and</li></ol></li><li id="_5f483b12-7a87-4d61-ac27-2ae607685b9a">a Class 9c <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1436_4.0.0.xml#_ed4b2daf-adce-4356-8317-77599f662b36" id="_0803bab8-ecc0-47f3-b08d-931b803ccade" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">residential care building</xref>; and</li><li id="_3d23c369-cdd9-49e5-99a8-39387a2c57eb">a Class 10a building or deck immediately adjacent or connected to a building of a type listed in (a) to (d).</li></ol></callout><callout id="_0b75860f-a29f-4edc-a9b7-76a5fa7106bd"><callout-type ncc-info-type="notes"/><p>For additional requirements relating to bushfire prone areas, refer to the Director’s Determinations on Bushfire Hazard Areas – current versions available at www.cbos.tas.gov.au</p></callout></clause>